RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 86. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOKAMAK bobbled and brushed outer rival leaving the gate, forwardly placed two then three wide on the first turn, bid three deep on the second bend, took a short lead while dueling with I GOT A GUY through the lane and dug in to prevail. I GOT A GUY sent for the front early then raced up close in the three path on the clubhouse turn, moved up to apply pressure on the backstretch then raced on even terms, vied with outer rivals late on the far turn, dueled inside TOKAMAK down the lane and finished gamely in defeat. PRAY FOR ME RAY broke a step slow, chased keenly in the two path under a hold early, raced between rivals into the second bend, angled out and came five wide into the drive, came with a late run outside the top pair but ran out of time. IVORY SKY dropped back off the pace and moved into the three path, bid four deep on the far turn, lost touch at the top of the stretch and churned on while unable to re-rally in the furlong grounds. SURE PROSPECT coaxed from the gate, raced in the two path off the pace early, moved into range in the middle stages, traveled along the rail then tipped two wide around trouble rival and could not produce a bid in the stretch. NUMBER ONE SON had to check when running up behind a rival on the first turn then steadied again at the three-quarter pole, moved closer three deep between rivals in the middle stages, lost ground on the far turn three to four wide and failed to menace. BRING HIM HOME trailed on the inside on the first turn, two wide into the lane and was not a factor. HILL SIXTEEN sped to the front and moved inside, pressured from outside on the backstretch, lost command on the far turn, roused with three furlongs left to run, pulled up shortly after, stopped in upper stretch and walked into the van following the race.

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, keen, 2wide, angled 5wide, late run

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 3wide, checked 1st & 3/4, 3wide into str, no menace

ENTRY.OWNER: Altamira Racing Stable CYBT Nentwig Michael and Weiner Daniel
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed inside, dueled inside, pulled up 2nd, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Tokamak
ENTRY.OWNER: Greco Pat and Cloonan Michael P

ENTRY.NAME: I Got a Guy
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent, up close 3wide, dueled outside, gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST IS showed the way three wide into the turn, moved into the two path around the bend, challenged RYDER'S CANDY approaching the stretch, responded to the when called upon and held the runner-up at bay. RYDER'S CANDY stalked two wide into the turn, bid inside JUST IS leaving the bend, lost touch briefly into the final furlong, kept on willingly in deep stretch but lacked the needed late punch to get by. ROSIE ANN RULES raced up close from outside, went five wide into the turn, angled down to the three path, came back out into the lane, weakened in the drive but finished a clear third. PLUM CREEK raced up close between early, four wide into the turn, moved down to the two path then got boxed in at the five-sixteenths pole, chased two wide into the drive and weakened. BLUE CLOUD trailed on the inside and came up empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000, if for $45,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SCREAMING VIRGINIA dropped back and trailed early, raced a bit off the rail around the bend, swung out past the five-sixteenths pole, closed well from the middle portion of the track and got up. BELLE EPOQUE forwardly placed from outside, bid three deep, fought five wide into the lane, took over and led clear into the final furlong but got caught in the closing moments. LADY CRUISER hit the gate, chased two wide into the turn, angled five to six wide leaving the bend, drifted in while closing and finished a game third. PRINCESS SNOW hit the gate, forwardly placed early from inside then challenged leaving the backstretch, fought three wide into the lane, drifted inward in the stretch and relinquished the lead to BELLE EPOQUE, then weakened in the final furlong. EASTER COMING BACK stepped to the front quickly, vied between rivals then chased the top pair in the two path leaving the bend and weakened. MISTY RAIN chased three wide leaving the backstretch, trailed four wide into the lane and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Snow
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate, vied inside-3wide, drifted in, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Screaming Virginia
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, inside, swung out, got up

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Cruiser
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate, chased 2wide, angled 5-6wide, drifted in, game 3rd

ENTRY.OWNER: Besecker Joseph E Diamant Eli Knight Scott and O'Neill Dennis

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 99. Starter Allowance Purse 21000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESTABLISHED stumbled and got bumped from outside leaving the gate, chased on the inside then two wide into the stretch, rallied steadily and drove past in the final fifty yards. OIL CAN KNIGHT set the pace under pressure from outer rival, shook free around the turn, showed the way three wide not the stretch, remained unchallenged into the final furlong but got run down in the final sixteenth. EL DIABLO ROJO got bumped and crowded in the beginning, stalked from outside, rounded the bend four then five wide and finished willingly for the show. PERFECT D broke in and bumped EL DIABLO ROJO, pressed the pace from outside, lost touch with the leader at the three-eighths pole, chased four wide into the drive and weakened in the furlong grounds. GROWTH ENGINE got bumped then crowded early, trailed three then four wide on the turn and was never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Oil Can Knight
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace inside, shook free 3/8, caught

ENTRY.NAME: Perfect D
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in/bumped, pressed outside, chased 4wide, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDERHEART was a bit antsy in the gate, dueled outside COMMANDER KHAI, disposed of that rival approaching the eighth pole and drew away. CATBERNAY brushed with outer rival early, chased two wide around the bend, moved out in the lane and finished willingly to earn the place honors. COMMANDER KHAI dueled for the lead from inside into and around the turn, battled to midstretch and weakened. STAFFORD TO KUPP antsy in the gate, brushed with inner rival and got put in tight early, chased three then four wide on the turn and lacked a bid. TRIBAL IMPACT laid off the pace early on, rounded the bend three to four wide and failed to threaten. ECHO ALPHA SIX fractious in the gate, trailed on the inside then two wide and was not a factor. HIGH PRESS chased widest near the back early, navigated the turn four to five wide and failed to menace. CONCH DADDY stumbled badly at the start and unseated the rider, caught by the outrider following the race and walked off. THE STEWARDS REVIEWED THE START OF CONCH DADDY AND RULED THAT HE CAUSED HIS OWN PROBLEMS AT THE START AND IS CONSIDERED A STARTER.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINNING BIG closest in pursuit from inside into the turn, chased two wide into the lane, rallied inside the leader and overtook that rival, then edged LAST CALL PAUL for the victory. LAST CALL PAUL forwardly placed four deep into the turn, continued four wide into the lane, rallied three deep late and got outclosed by the winner. SMILING JOJO broke in, sped clear to take control, padded the lead two then three wide on the turn, held a diminished lead entering the final furlong and yielded to rivals on both sides in deep stretch. TWILIGHT MOON broke slow and bumped leaving the gate, climbed a bit and dropped back, angled in on the turn, steered back out approaching the stretch and improved position. GRAZEN BOY tracked four wide into the turn, moved out and entered the lane eight wide and failed to respond to urging. BEAR COAST bumped with outer rival at the start, chased under coaxing two then three wide and weakened down the lane. UNCLE JUJU bumped with inner rival early, chased three deep into the turn, exited the bend five wide and faded. PICAHOUSE bumped with outer rival early, chased in the two path then along the rail, ducked out from the left hand in upper stretch and had little left for the late stages.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow/bumped, climbed bit, angled in/out turn, improved

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SCATIFY hit the gate to lose a step at the start, chased three deep early, bid three deep or four wide on the turn, fought three wide into the lane, took over past the quarter pole, battled with MARCH OF TIME through the final furlong and held gamely. MARCH OF TIME stalked from inside early, steadied a bit into the turn, bid inside the leader entering the lane, dueled inside SCATIFY down the stretch and finished gamely in defeat. BATTLE CRUISER broke a step slow and got crowded at the start, trailed off the inside, angled to the rail for the turn, moved back out in the lane and was along for the show. BENEFICIAL brushed the gate but was still away alertly, dueled for the lead from inside then cleared up the backstretch, held a short lead two wide into the lane, relinquished the lead between rivals at the top of the stretch and weakened down the lane. SHARP LORENZO bobbled at the start, chased keenly between early, rounded the bend in the two path, steered out in the lane and lacked a rally. HONEST COOP dueled for the lead from outside then chased the leader leaving the backstretch, re-bid between rivals on the turn, failed to sustain the challenge and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 33000. FOR FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000, if for $28,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOSSY BRUIN GAL coaxed from the gate, chased two wide around the turn, tipped three wide leaving the bend, drifted out midstretch while offering a bid between rivals and bested WOK DON'T RUN in deep stretch for the victory. WOK DON'T RUN got pinched back at the start, chased from outside early, bid three deep at the five-sixteenths pole, fought five wide into the lane, took over in upper stretch, held command into the final furlong but got outkicked by BOSSY BRUIN GAL in the late stages. MISS PIXY STIX brushed between rivals at the start, got crowded shortly after, tracked three wide into the turn, angled six wide leaving the bend, rallied widest and finished a game third. BELLA VIENNA hit the gate then went up to take control, dueled inside a rival around the bend and two wide into the stretch, lost command at the top of the lane, fought into the furlong grounds and weakened in the final sixteenth. KATALEYA pressed the pace from outside, dueled around the turn, came four wide into the stretch, drifted in midstretch and weakened. UNIFIED A. P. stalked from inside, cut the corner into the lane and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Los Alamitos Futurity - Grade2 LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 96. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. By subscription of $300 each to accompany the nomination on or before August 31st, 2023 closed with 34. For horses not nominated, supplementary nominations of $7,500 each will close at the time of entry. All horses shall pay $1,500 to p ass the entry box and $2,500 additional to start, with $200,000 Guaranteed of which $120,000 to first, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. 120 lbs. . A trophy will be presented to the winning owner, trainer and jock ey. ey. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WYNSTOCK hustled to the front from inside and led two wide through the clubhouse turn, showed the way up the backstretch, tested by WINE ME UP at the five-sixteenths pole, put away that rival at the quarter pole but was immediately confronted by STRONGHOLD from inside, brushed lightly by that rival midstretch then came in and bumped at the eighth pole while losing command, fought back gamely and bested the runner-up in the final sixteenth. STRONGHOLD pulled early when rated then chased in the two path, saved ground through the far turn, challenged WYNSTOCK from inside past the quarter pole, drifted out and brushed that rival lightly midstretch, took a bump from that rival while gaining a slim advantage at the eight pole but was outkicked in the late stages. COACH PRIME chased three to four wide on the clubhouse turn, navigated the second bend four then five wide, summoned a mild rally and gained the show honors while closing the gap on the top pair. WINE ME UP forwardly placed four wide through the first turn, chased three deep leaving the backstretch, bid three wide outside WYNSTOCK at the five-sixteenths pole, fought four wide into the lane, failed to sustain the challenge with a quarter mile left to run and flattened in the late stages. ACE OF CLUBS raced up close in the three path early, chased between rivals in the two path into the far turn, entered the lane three wide and weakened in the stretch run. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE STRETCH RUN BETWEEN WYNSTOCK AND STRONGHOLD. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT BOTH RIVALS CONTRIBUTED TO THE INCIDENT AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.

ENTRY.NAME: Wynstock
ENTRY.OWNER: Allred Edward C and Liebau Jack
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled, cleared 2path, met bids, drifted in/bumped 1/8, dug in

ENTRY.NAME: Stronghold
ENTRY.OWNER: Waller Eric M and Waller Sharon
ENTRY.COMMENT: pulled, 2wide-inside, bid inside, drifted out, bumped 1/8, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Ace of Clubs
ENTRY.OWNER: ERJ Racing LLC Fritz Brothers Racing LLC Pappas Horse Racing Corp and Suarez Pab
